Build succeeds with 0 errors. Here's the fix:

**The change:** Add `: base(null)` to your constructor call. In MSTest v4, `TestMethodAttribute` removed its parameterless constructor and now requires a `string? displayName` parameter. Passing `null` preserves the default behavior (method name is used as display name).

```csharp
public CategorizedTestMethodAttribute(string category) : base(null)
{
    Category = category;
}
```

If you want the category to also serve as the display name, you could pass `category` instead of `null`.
